title: Design an academic, musky, and vintage logo for a craft cocktail collective and consulting business
slogan_to_incorporate: “Cocktail Collective” and/or some variation of “Estd. 2022” if you can make it look good
description: Professor Proof is a craft cocktail collective and consulting business that offers luxury, private bartending services, creative teaching experiences, and restaurant consultations. We pride ourselves in our approach to creating truly unique recipes, our high levels of customization to create memorable experiences for customers, and our efforts to creatively educate about all aspects of what makes a well-curated drink equally beautiful and delicious.
other_notes:
I’d like to incorporate a professorial-type man who is wearing a flat cap, bar apron, and/or is stirring a cocktail. We want our colors to remain in the area of green, brown, gray, and possibly navy blue or black. A small red accent could also work if navy blue is involved. Our branding wants integrate one or more of the following styles/elements: academic, rustic, masculine, luxury, gracefully disheveled, refined, Scottish tweed, rounded tortoise shell glasses, flat cap.
Update:
A few clarifying tidbits: a flat cap is not a top hat or a baseball cap but, rather, a hat that is worn by many Scottish farmers.
I’ve omitted beard as one of the elements to incorporate. If any facial hair should be involved, only light scruff (read: 5 o’clock shadow) should be involved.
The glasses should be regular eyeglasses, not sunglasses.
I’ve also chosen the to let you all choose your colors, though I have given some direction here. Just make it creative!
Update #2:
Incorporating a beige/sepia background looks the most aesthetically pleasing for this design.
The bust of the bartender should have a diverted gaze.
Thank you and let me know if you have any questions!
Update #3
Please incorporate different handwritten fonts into the logo. The fonts should look more organic while still keeping a refined feel.
I have been seeing a lot of sport coats/blazers that the person is wearing. The brief mentions that he should be wearing an apron.
Final round update #1:
First of all thank you all for your hard work and making it the final round. All of your designs look very nice and I’m looking forward to seeing the revisions made in this round.
1. Change all “Estd. 2022” to “MEM TEN”. Our business is based in Memphis, Tennessee (USA) and I think that is more appropriate for the logo until we start doing business in other areas. You are more than welcome to use all capital letters or a combination of capital letters and lowercase letters as well. Just make it look nice :)
2. Take a closer look at the pictures I shared of my face and integrate some aspects of the picture and incorporate it into the design. Some combination of masculine and feminine should be in the face, but it should look more masculine. Many you have already done this but I think, overall, there needs a bit more work on the face.
3. If you can incorporate soft, muted colors into the graphic and typography, I think it would be a better fit for the overall branding. I still really like the muted, beige background so feel free to keep it!
Thank you all again for your hard work. We really appreciate your time and effort. We look forward to seeing some revisions. Please feel free to send me a direct message if there any questions!
Happy designing! 🥃
